       Name: Iron Resolve
       Kind: Skill
     Target: TAR_IGNORE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 0
 Wait Beats: 24
 Can Learn: TRUE
Noun Damage: None
   Wear-Off: Your iron resolve fades.
Acquisition:
   - Crusader: level 10
Description:
   Iron Resolve plants the Crusader's feet and steels their fighting
   position, granting an AC bonus for several rounds. This defensive buff
   protects combo chains from being disrupted by position-changing effects
   like bash knockdowns.

   The Solar Court Crusader designation honored practitioners who served
   successive engagements without rotation. Iron Resolve is the mechanical
   expression of that continuous-service identity -- the formation
   discipline that anchors Crusader combat.

   Costs: Movement (via subtract_energy_cost)
   Cooldown: 15 rounds
   Duration: 3 + (Crusader level / 5) rounds
   AC modifier: -(Crusader level * 3)

   Distinct from Fortify (Warden passive defense): Iron Resolve is
   specifically about maintaining fighting position to protect combo
   building, not general damage reduction.
